Profiling allows you to see which code uses how much of computer's resources during generation. Each generation writes its own profile to one file, overwriting previous. The file can be viewed in Chrome, or on a Perfetto web site. Warning: writing profile can take a lot of time, up to 30 seconds, and the file itelf can be around 500MB in size.

sd_vae_explanation.title: Sd Vae Explanation
sd_vae_explanation.default:
<abbr title='Variational autoencoder'>VAE</abbr> is a neural network that transforms a standard <abbr title='red/green/blue'>RGB</abbr>
image into latent space representation and back. Latent space representation is what stable diffusion is working on during sampling
(i.e. when the progress bar is between empty and full). For txt2img, VAE is used to create a resulting image after the sampling is finished.
For img2img, VAE is used to process user's input image before the sampling, and to create an image after sampling.
